.TH JTUTIL-GH-BUILD "1" "June 2026" "jtutil-gh-build manual" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jtutil-gh-build \- Run a remote GitHub FPGA build and download the artifact
.SH DESCRIPTION
Triggers the compile-custom GitHub Actions workflow for one or more cores and a
comma-separated target list, waits for the run to finish, and downloads the
matching release artifacts into $JTROOT/release.
.PP
The GitHub CLI
.BR gh (1)
must be installed and authenticated with access to the jtcores GitHub
repository. The workflow file must already exist on GitHub's default branch for
manual
.B workflow_dispatch
runs to be accepted.
.PP
The target list is passed with
.B -t
or
.B --target
as a comma-separated pflag string slice. Common examples are:
.IP
jtutil gh-build cps3 -t mister,pocket
.IP
jtutil gh-build cps3 --target sidi,sidi128
.IP
jtutil gh-build 1942 gng kicker --target sidi,mist
.IP
jtutil gh-build cps3 -t mist
.PP
The
.B mist
target uses the Quartus 13 Docker image in its own matrix job. Other targets
use the Quartus 20 Docker image.
.PP
The GitHub workflow compiles each core and target combination in a separate
matrix job so GitHub can run them in parallel on different runners. For
example, three cores with two targets request six compile jobs.
.PP
By default,
.B jtutil gh-build
uses
.B gh run watch
for interactive progress. Use
.B --batch
from scripts and tools that should avoid the full-screen terminal progress
display. Batch mode still polls the workflow and prints an update when each
GitHub job finishes.
.PP
After the remote run finishes successfully,
.B jtutil gh-build
downloads each matching release artifact, such as
.B release-mister-cps3
and
.BR release-sidi-gng ,
creates
.B $JTROOT/release
if needed, and extracts it there.
.SS "Usage:"
.IP
jtutil gh-build <core> [core...] [flags]
.SS "Flags:"
.TP
.BR \-\-batch
Poll without full-screen terminal updates
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
help for gh-build
.TP
.BR \-\-ref " string"
Git ref that contains the workflow file
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-target " strings"
Comma-separated list of FPGA targets
.SS "Global Flags:"
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Verbose
